VERDICT (2026-06-18, sol): worst-b internal term geometry is GENERIC EVT large-deviation, no lever.

SAMPLING CAVEAT (honesty, per codex): for n=64,128 the "worst b" is a SAMPLED maximum over 60k of
the (p-1)/n quotient reps, NOT the true argmax. This does NOT weaken the verdict, for two reasons:
  (a) a sampled max is a LOWER bound on the true M, so it can only UNDERSTATE R1; and
  (b) the true worst-b R1 is bounded ABOVE unconditionally by the Cauchy-Schwarz brick
